Could Not Be Made for the Seal Documents Identified . . . 7  
 
 
4.   Current Nationwide Concern Has Heightened the Public's Need 
for Access . . . 8  
 
5.   At a Minimum the Court Should Release the Search Warrant 
Documents in Redacted Form . . . 14  
 
RELIEF REQUESTED . . . 15 
 
 
TABLE OF AUTHORITIES 
 
CASES 
 
Matter of Application and Affidavit for a Search Warrant, 923 F.2d  
324)  (4th  Cir.  1991),  cert.  denied, Hughes v. Washington Post 
Co., 500 U.S. 944, 111 S. Ct. 2243, 114 L.Ed.2d 484 (1991) .  
 
Application of National Broadcasting Co., Inc., 828 F.2d 340 (6th 
Cir. 1987)  
 
Associated Press v. U.S. District Court for Cent. Dist. of Col., 705 
F.2d 1143 (9th Cir. 1983)  
 
Baltimore Sun Co. v. Goetz, 886 F.2d 60 (4th Cir. 1989)  
 
Brown & Williamson Tobacco Corp. v. Federal Trade 
Commission, 710 F.2d 1165, (6th Cir.  1983), cert. denied, 465 
U.S. 1100, 104 S.Ct. 1595, 80 L.Ed.2d 127 (1984)  
 
CBS, Inc. v. Young, 522 F.2d 234 (6th Cir. 1975)  
 
Certain Interested Individuals v. Pulitzer Publishing Co., 895 F.2d 
460 (8th Cir. 1990), cert. denied, Pulitzer Pub. Co. v. Certain 
Interested Individuals, 498 U.S. 880,111 S.Ct. 214, 112 L.Ed.2d 
173 (1990) (Gunn II)  
 
