<HR WIDTH="525" ALIGN=LEFT>

<P>Title: "First Day, Tuesday, 11/20/1945, Part 8: Appendix C: Charges and Particulars of Violations of International Treaties, Agreements and Assuracncs Causes By The Defendants In The Course of Planning, Preparing and Initiating the Wars", in Trial of the Major War Criminals before the International Military Tribunal. Volume II. Proceedings: 11/14/1945-11/30/1945. [Official text in the English language.] Nuremberg: IMT, 1947. pp. 87-89.</P>

<P>Author: International Military Tribunal</P>

<P>Accession Number: AC_94X_00261</P>

<P>Publication Date: PD_19470101.</P>

<P>Document Type: Government Document.</P>

<P>Source Document Language(s): English</P>

<P>See Also Related Document Supersets: 2IMT; IMT; NWCT</P>

<P>Country of Publication: Germany</P>

<P>Full Text:</P>

<P>SIR DAVID MAXWELL-FYFE (Continuing the reading of the Indictment):</P>

<P> Violation of the Convention for the Pacific Settlement of International Disputes signed at The Hague, 29 July 1899.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, by force and arms, on the dates specified in Column 1, invade the territory of the Sovereigns specified in Column 2, respectively, without first having attempted to settle its disputes with said Sovereigns by pacific means.</P>

<P>Column 1: 4/6/1941, Column 2: Kingdom of Greece; Column 1: 4/6/1941, Column 2: Kingdom of Yugoslavia</P>

<P> Violation of the Convention for the Pacific Settlement of International Disputes, signed at The Hague, 10/18/1907.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about the dates specified in Column 1, by force of arms invade the territory of the Sovereigns specified in Column 2, respectively, without having first attempted to settle its dispute with said Sovereigns by pacific means.</P>

<P>Column 1: 9/1/1939, Column 2: Republic of Poland; 4/9/1940, Kingdom of Norway; 4/9/1940, Kingdom of Denmark; 5/10/1940, Grand Duchy of Luxembourg; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of Belgium; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of the Netherlands; 6/22/1941, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics</P>

<P>III. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of Hague Convention III Relative to the Opening of Hostilities, Signed 10/18/1907.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about the dates specified in Column 1, commence hostilities against the Countries specified in Column 2, respectively, without previous warning in the form of a reasoned declaration of war or an ultimatum with conditional declaration of war.</P>

<P>Column 1: 9/1/1939, Column 2: Republic of Poland; 4/9/1940, Kingdom of Norway; 4/9/1940, Kingdom of Denmark; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of Belgium; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of the Netherlands; 5/10/1940, Grand Duchy of Luxembourg; 6/22/1941, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics</P>

<P> Violation of Hague Convention V Respecting the Rights and Duties of Neutral Powers and Persons in Case of War on Land, signed 10/18/1907.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about the dates specified in Column 1, by force and arms of its military forces, cross into, invade, and occupy the territories of the Sovereigns specified in Column 2, respectively, then and thereby violating the neutrality of said Sovereigns.</P>

<P>Column 1: 4/9/1940, Column 2: Kingdom of Norway; 4/9/1940, Kingdom of Denmark; 5/10/1940, Grand Duchy of Luxembourg; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of Belgium; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of the Netherlands; 6/22/1941, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics</P>

<P> Violation of the Treaty of Peace between the Allied and Associated Powers and Germany, signed at Versailles, 6/28/1919, known as the Versailles Treaty.</P>

<P>Particulars: (1) In that Germany did, on and after 3/7/1936, maintain and assemble armed forces and maintain and construct military fortifications in the demilitarized zone of the Rhineland in violation of the provisions of Articles 42-44 of the Treaty of Versailles.</P>

<P>(2) In that Germany did, on or about 3/13/1938, annex Austria into the German Reich in violation of the provisions of Article 80 of the Treaty of Versailles.</P>

<P>(3) In that Germany did, on or about 3/22/1939, incorporate the district of Memel into the German Reich in violation of the provisions of Article 99 of the Treaty of Versailles.</P>

<P>(4) In that Germany did, on or about 9/1/1939, incorporate the Free City of Danzig into the German Reich in violation of the provisions of Article 100 of the Treaty of Versailles.</P>

<P>(5) In that Germany did, on or about 3/16/1939, incorporate the Provinces of Bohemia and Moravia, formerly part of Czechoslovakia, into the German Reich in violation of the provisions of Article 81 of the Treaty of Versailles.</P>

<P>(6) In that Germany did, at various times in 3/1935 and thereafter, repudiate various parts of Part V, Military, Naval, and Air Clauses of the Treaty of Versailles, by creating an air force, by use of compulsory military service, by increasing the size of the army beyond treaty limits, and by increasing the size of the navy beyond treaty limits.</P>

<P> Violation of the Treaty between the United States and Germany Restoring Friendly Relations, signed at Berlin, 8/25/1921.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, at various times in 3/1935 and thereafter, repudiate various parts of Part V, Military, Naval, and Air Clauses of the Treaty between the United States and Germany Restoring Friendly Relations by creating an air force, by use of compulsory military service, by increasing the size of the army beyond treaty limits, and by increasing the size of the navy beyond treaty limits.</P>

<P>VII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of the Treaty of Mutual Guarantee between Germany, Belgium, France, Great Britain, and Italy, done at Locarno, 10/16/1925.</P>

<P>Particulars: (1) In that Germany did, on or about 3/7/1936, unlawfully send armed forces into the Rhineland demilitarized zone of Germany, in violation of Article 1 of the Treaty of Mutual Guarantee.</P>

<P>(2) In that Germany did, in or about 3/1936, and thereafter, unlawfully maintain armed forces in the Rhineland demilitarized zone of Germany, in violation of Article 1 of the Treaty of Mutual Guarantee.</P>

<P>(3) In that Germany did, on or about 3/7/1936, and thereafter, unlawfully construct and maintain fortifications in the Rhineland demilitarized zone of Germany, in violation of Article l of the Treaty of Mutual Guarantee.</P>

<P>(4) In that Germany did, on or about 5/10/1940, unlawfully attack and invade Belgium, in violation of Article 2 of the Treaty of Mutual Guarantee.</P>

<P>(5) In that Germany did, on or about 5/10/1940, unlawfully attack and invade Belgium, without first having attempted to settle its dispute with Belgium by peaceful means, in violation of Article 3 of the Treaty of Mutual Guarantee.</P>

<P>VIII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of the Arbitration Treaty between Germany and Czechoslovakia, done at Locarno, 10/16/1925.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about 3/15/1939, unlawfully by duress and threats of military might force Czechoslovakia to deliver the destiny of Czechoslovakia and its inhabitants into the hands of the Fuehrer and Reichschancellor of Germany without having attempted to settle its dispute with Czechoslovakia by peaceful means.</P>

<P> Violation of the Arbitration Convention between Germany and Belgium, done at Locarno, 10/16/1925.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about 5/10/1940, unlawfully attack and invade Belgium without first having attempted to settle its dispute with Belgium by peaceful means.</P>

<P> Violation of the Arbitration Treaty between Germany and Poland, done at Locarno, 10/16/1925.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about 9/1/1939, unlawfully attack and invade Poland without first having attempted to settle its dispute with Poland by peaceful means.</P>

<P> Violation of Convention of Arbitration and Conciliation entered into between Germany and the Netherlands or 5/20/1926.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany, without warning, and notwithstanding its solemn covenant to settle by peaceful means all disputes of any nature whatever which might arise between it and the Netherlands which were not capable of settlement by diplomacy and which had not been referred by mutual agreement to the Permanent Court of International Justice, did, on or about 5/10/1940 with a military force, attack, invade, and occupy the Netherlands, thereby violating its neutrality and territorial integrity and destroying its sovereign independence.</P>

<P>XII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of Convention of Arbitration and Conciliation entered into between Germany and Denmark on 6/2/1926.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany, without warning, and notwithstanding its solemn covenant to settle by peaceful means all disputes of any nature whatever which might arise between it and Denmark which were not capable of settlement by diplomacy and which had not been referred by mutual agreement to the Permanent Court of International Justice, did, on or about 4/9/1940, with a military force, attack, invade, and occupy Denmark, thereby violating its neutrality and territorial integrity and destroying its sovereign independence.</P>

<P>XIII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of Treaty between Germany and other Powers providing for Renunciation of War as an Instrument of National Policy, signed at Paris 8/27/1928, known as the Kellogg-Briand Pact.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about the dates specified in Column 1, with a military force, attack the Sovereigns specified in Column 2, respectively, and resort to war against such Sovereigns, in violation of its solemn declaration condemning recourse to war for the solution of international controversies, its solemn renunciation of war as an instrument of national policy in its relations with such Sovereigns, and its solemn covenant that settlement or solution of all disputes or conflicts of whatever nature or origin arising between it and such Sovereigns should never be sought except by pacific means.</P>

<P>Column 1: 9/1/1939, Column 2: Republic of Poland; 4/9/1940, Kingdom of Norway; 4/9/1940, Kingdom of Denmark; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of Belgium; 5/10/1940, Grand Duchy of Luxembourg; 5/10/1940, Kingdom of the Netherlands; 4/6/1941, Kingdom of Greece; 4/6/1941, Kingdom of Yugoslavia; 6/2/1941, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics; 12/11/1941, United States of America</P>

<P>XIV. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of Treaty of Arbitration and Conciliation entered into between Germany and Luxembourg on 9/11/1929.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany. without warning. and notwithstanding its solemn covenant to settle by peaceful means all disputes which might arise between it and Luxembourg which were not capable of settlement by diplomacy, did, on or about 5/10/1940 with a military force, attack, invade, and occupy Luxembourg, thereby violating its neutrality and territorial integrity and destroying its sovereign independence.</P>

<P> Violation of the Declaration of Non-Aggression entered into between Germany and Poland on 1/26/1934.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany proceeding to the application of force for the purpose of reaching a decision did, on or about 9/1/1939, at various places along the German-Polish frontier employ military forces to attack, invade, and commit other acts of aggression against Poland.</P>

<P>XVI. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of German Assurance given on 5/21/1935 that the Inviolability and Integrity of the Federal State of Austria Would Be Recognized.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany did, on or about 3/11/1938, at various points and places along the German-Austria frontier, with a military force and in violation of its solemn declaration and assurance, invade and annex to Germany the territory of the Federal State of Austria.</P>

<P>XVII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of Austro-German Agreement of 7/11/1936.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany during the period from 2/12/1938-3/13/1938 did by duress and various aggressive acts, including the use of military force, cause the Federal State of Austria to yield up its sovereignty to the German State in violation of Germany's agreement to recognize the full sovereignty of the Federal State of Austria.</P>

<P>XVIII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of German Assurances given on 1/30/1937, 4/28/1939, 8/26/1939, and 10/6/1939 To Respect the Neutrality and Territorial Inviolability of the Netherlands.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany, without warning, and without recourse to peaceful means of settling any considered differences did, on or about 5/10/1940, with a military force and in violation of its solemn assurances, invade, occupy, and attempt to subjugate the sovereign territory of the Netherlands.</P>

<P>XIX. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of German Assurances given on 1/30/1937, 10/13/1937, 4/28/1939, 8/26/1939, and 10/6/1939 To Respect the Neutrality and Territorial Integrity and Inviolability of Belgium.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany, without warning, did on or about 5/10/1940, with a military force and in violation of its solemn assurances and declarations, attack, invade, and occupy the sovereign territory of Belgium.</P>

<P> Violation of Assurances given on 3/11/1938-9/26/1938 to Czechoslovakia.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany, on or about 3/15/1939 did, by establishing a Protectorate of Bohemia and Moravia under duress and by the threat of force, violate the assurance given on 3/11/1938 to respect the territorial integrity of the Czechoslovak Republic and the assurance given on 9/26/1938 that, if the so-called Sudeten territories were ceded to Germany, no further German territorial claims on Czechoslovakia would be made.</P>

<P>XXI. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of the Munich Agreement and Annexes of 9/29/1938.</P>

<P>Particulars: (1) In that Germany on or about 3/15/1939, did by duress and the threat of military intervention force the Republic of Czechoslovakia to deliver the destiny of the Czech people and country into the hands of the Fuehrer of the German Reich.</P>

<P>(2) In that Germany refused and failed to join in an international guarantee of the new boundaries of the Czechoslovakia state as provided for in Annex No. 1 to the Munich Agreement.</P>

<P>XXII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of the Solemn Assurances of Germany given on 9/3/1939, 4/28/1939, and 10/6/1939 Not To Violate the Independence or Sovereignty of the Kingdom of Norway.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany, without warning did, on or about 4/10/1940, with its military and naval forces attack, invade, and commit other acts of aggression against the Kingdom of Norway.</P>

<P>XXIII. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of German Assurances given on 4/28/1939-8/26/1939 To Respect the Neutrality and Territorial Inviolability of Luxembourg.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany, without warning, and without recourse to peaceful means of settling any considered differences, did, on or about 5/10/1940, with a military force and in violation of the solemn assurances, invade, occupy, and absorb into Germany the sovereign territory of Luxembourg.</P>

<P>XXIV. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of the Treaty of Non-Aggression between Germany and Denmark, signed at Berlin, 5/31/1939.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany without prior warning, did. on or about 4/9/1940, with its military forces, attack, invade. and commit other acts of aggression against the Kingdom of Denmark.</P>

<P>XXV. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of Treaty of Non-Aggression entered into between Germany and USSR on 8/23/1939.</P>

<P>Particulars: (1) In that Germany did, on or about 6/22/1941, employ military forces to attack and commit acts of aggression against the USSR</P>

<P>(2) In that Germany without warning or recourse to a friendly exchange of views or arbitration did, on or about 6/22/1941, employ military forces to attack and commit acts of aggression against the USSR</P>

<P>XXVI. Charge:</P>

<P>Violation of German Assurance given on 10/6/1939 To Respect the Neutrality and Territorial Integrity of Yugoslavia.</P>

<P>Particulars: In that Germany without prior warning did, on or about 4/6/1941, with its military forces attack, invade, and commit other acts of aggression against the Kingdom of Yugoslavia.</P>

<P>THE PRESIDENT: The Tribunal will now adjourn until 10 o'clock tomorrow morning.</P>

<P>[The Tribunal adjourned until 11/21/1945 at 1000 hours.]. [=]</P>

